<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Constructive_geometry  
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Constructive_geometry"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Constructive_geometry">
A <b>Constructive_geometry</b> is a  type of <b>Representation</b>.  It represents a collection of geometric elements used to support the definition of a <b>Geometric_model</b>. 
<p>
Each <b>Constructive_geometry</b> shall be associated with at least a <b>Geometric_model</b> or another <b>Constructive_geometry</b>, through an instance of <b>Constructive_geometry_association</b>.
</p>
</ext_description>
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Constructive_geometry.context_of_items">
	the <b>Geometric_coordinate_space</b> in which the geometric elements are defined.
		</ext_description>

  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Constructive_geometry.wr:WR1">
the <b>Constructive_geometry</b>	shall only contain instances of types listed in <b>constructive_element_select</b> type or in its extensions.
	</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Constructive_geometry  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Constructive_geometry.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Constructive_geometry.name">
the group of words by which the <b>Construction_geometry</b> is known.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Constructive_geometry_association  
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Constructive_geometry_association"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Constructive_geometry_association">
	A <b>Constructive_geometry_association</b> is the association of an auxiliary <b>Constructive_geometry</b> with a <b>Geometric_model</b> or another <b>Constructive_geometry</b>. This association specifies that the auxiliary <b>Constructive_geometry</b> contains elements that have been used to build the elements of the <b>Geometric_model</b> or of the <b>Constructive_geometry</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Constructive_geometry_association  Attribute: auxiliary_geometry 
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Constructive_geometry_association.auxiliary_geometry"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Constructive_geometry_association.auxiliary_geometry">
	the <b>Constructive_geometry</b> that supports the definition of the base_geometry.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Constructive_geometry_association  Attribute: base_geometry 
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Constructive_geometry_association.base_geometry"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Constructive_geometry_association.base_geometry">
	the <b>Geometric_model</b> or the <b>Constructive_geometry</b> for which the auxiliary geometry was used.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Constructive_geometry_association  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Constructive_geometry_association.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Constructive_geometry_association.description">
	a text that provides additional information about the <b>Constructive_geometry_association</b>.
</ext_description>

  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Constructive_geometry_association.wr:WR1">
the geometric coordinate space of the base geometry and the auxiliary geometry shall be the same. </ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Curve  
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Curve"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Curve">
	A <b>Curve</b> is a type of <b>Detailed_geometric_model_element</b>.It represents a path of a point moving in 3-dimensional coordinate space.
	A <b>Curve</b> is defined with a mono-parametric continuous function applied on an interval of R (set of real values).
	<note>
	The <b>Curve</b> entity  is a supertype of various specific kinds of curves. 
	The definition of these specific types is outside the scope of the present module.
	</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Line  
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Line"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Line">
	A <b>Line</b> is a type of <b>Curve</b>. It represents an infinite straight path.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Measurement_path  
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Measurement_path"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Measurement_path">
	A <b>Measurement_path</b> is a mechanism to identify a <b>Curve</b> along which a given geometric dimension or surface texture may be fulfilled.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Measurement_path  Attribute: defined_by 
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Measurement_path.defined_by"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Measurement_path.defined_by">
	the <b>Curve</b> along which the measurement takes place.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Measurement_path  Attribute: defined_in 
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Measurement_path.defined_in"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Measurement_path.defined_in">
	the <b>Cartesian_coordinate_space</b> that identifies the context in which the measurement path is evaluated.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Plane  
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Plane"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Plane">
	A <b>Plane</b> is a type of <b>Surface</b>. It represenets a flat, infinite surface.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Point_on_curve  
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Point_on_curve"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Point_on_curve">
	A <b>Point_on_curve</b> is a type of <b>Detailed_geometric_model_element</b>.  It represents a point which lies on a curve.
It results from the evaluation of the function that defines the <b>Curve</b> with a particular parameter.
</ext_description>

  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Point_on_curve.supporting_curve">
the <b>Curve</b> onto which the point is evaluated.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Point_on_surface  
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Point_on_surface"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Point_on_surface">
	A <b>Point_on_surface</b> is a type of <b>Detailed_geometric_model_element</b>. It represents a point that lies on a parametric surface.
It  results either from the evaluation of the function that defines the <b>Surface</b> with a particular couple of parameters or from the evaluation of a point where a curve on the surface collapses.
</ext_description>

  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Point_on_surface.supporting_surface">
the <b>Surface</b> onto which the point is evaluated.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Construction_geometry_arm  Entity: Surface  
   <express_ref linkend="construction_geometry:arm:Construction_geometry_arm.Surface"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Construction_geometry_arm.Surface">
	A <b>Surface</b> is a type of <b>Detailed_geometric_model_element</b>.
It represents a set of mathematical points located in 3D space. 
	A <b>Surface</b> is defined with a bi-parametric continuous function applied on a connected subset of R2 (set of couples of real values).
<note number="1">A <b>Surface</b> may not be manifold.</note>
	<note number="2">
	The <b>Surface</b> entity is a supertype of various specific kinds of surfaces. The definition of these specific types is outside the scope of the present module.</note>
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
